# Cline rules — shared source of truth (agent-constitution)

Cline does not read the agent-constitution rules or CLAUDE.md automatically. This file
points every project at the same source of truth. Installed per project by install.sh
(symlink → .agent/constitution/templates/.clinerules); update the constitution to update all.

## Task source of truth
ALL tasks live in ONE central file: `~/.local/share/agent-projects/_memory/TODO.md`
- Read the `## <project>` section (project = this repo's name, lowercased) **and** `## 🌐 Cross-project`.
- Add or complete tasks THERE — never create a per-repo `TODO.md`.

## Personal data → vault, never the repo
Personal data (API keys, CVs, `SESSION.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, transcripts) lives in
`~/.local/share/agent-projects/<project>/`, never in the repo. Shared LLM keys:
`~/.local/share/agent-projects/_shared/secrets/.env`. (See rule `035-data-vault`.)

## Rules & git
This repo links the constitution at `.agent/constitution/` (a central clone, NOT a
submodule). Before acting, read `.agent/constitution/rules/000-core.md` and `040-git.md`.
- Branch first; never commit to `main`/`master`.
- NEVER add AI attribution to commits (`Co-Authored-By: Claude`, "Generated with…", 🤖) — rule `040-git`.
- Update docs before staging; no silent errors (log anything unfixed in the central TODO).
